<p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.16611889232116206">The  aim of any development organization is to reach as many people as  possible and have as great an impact as possible. CIP’s Impact  Assessment Unit employs a range of methods and disciplines to evaluate  what is working, and where funding can best be put to use.</span><br /><span></span><br /><span>Scientists  have developed a number of techniques and tools which serve as a  compass for projects. Research not only follows up returns on  investment, but also identifies a diverse set of impact indicators and  develops the methodologies for effectively measuring and monitoring  them. </span><br /><span></span><br /><span>Improving targeting - doing a better job of monitoring impact</span><br /><span></span><br /><span>To  find an effective way of measuring and monitoring progress, and  increasing impact across each of CIP’s regional and global priority  areas, scientists have developed improved methodologies for impact  targeting, and needs and opportunities assessment. These research  methods can be applied globally or for very specific technology</span></p>